deployment/timemaster/timemaster-baremet.message:
Thinking out loud here, these settings are from chrony-baremetal-ansible.yaml [1], any change in this file has to be manually replicated here to which is error prone. Instead it is possible to create a resource for the chrony-baremetal-ansible.yaml service, from which ansible_group_vars canbe reused, with additional mertgin of ptp_interfaces and ptp_transport. some thing like, 


resources:
  ...
  ChronyBase:
    type: ./../timesync/chrony-baremetal-ansible.yaml
    properties:
      ServiceData: {get_param: ServiceData}
      ServiceNetMap: {get_param: ServiceNetMap}
      DefaultPasswords: {get_param: DefaultPasswords}
      EndpointMap: {get_param: EndpointMap}
      RoleName: {get_param: RoleName}
      RoleParameters: {get_param: RoleParameters}

outputs:
  role_data:
    value:
      ...
      ansible_group_vars:
        map_merge:
          - get_attr: [ChronyBase, role_data, ansible_group_vars]
          - ptp_interfaces: {get_attr: [RoleParametersValue, value, tripleo_ptp_interfaces]}
            ptp_transport: {get_attr: [RoleParametersValue, value, tripleo_ptp_transport]}


[1] https://github.com/openstack/tripleo-heat-templates/blob/50367fbe3563d34976deb377ed32b6f26aeca44f/deployment/timesync/chrony-baremetal-ansible.yaml#L124

